    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-10-13T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-10-13T06:00:00-05:00" n="259"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d259">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">310.2/10–1351: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thompson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-10-13T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 13, 1951—noon.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1694. In an after-dinner conversation last night, the Prime Minister asked me to
                    forward the following suggestion:</p>
                <p>He believes that we miss a propaganda advantage by constantly being forced to
                    take a negative attitude to Soviet proposals. He, therefore, suggests that
                    instead of saying no to the Soviet suggestion that Bulgaria, Hungary and Rumania
                    be admitted to the <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>, we should state that we
                    would welcome and support their applications for membership as soon as they can
                    produce evidence that they are free and democratic.</p>
                <p>Sent <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> 1694; repeated info Moscow 30.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thompson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
